    Provides classes and interfaces related to working with the Open Service Broker API.

      A ServiceBroker that multiplexes other ServiceBrokers.

      protected ServiceBroker CompositeServiceBroker.getServiceBrokerForServiceId(String serviceId)
      Returns the ServiceBroker logically responsible for the logical Catalog.Service identified by the supplied serviceId, or null if no such ServiceBroker exists.
      protected ServiceBroker CompositeServiceBroker.putServiceBrokerForServiceId(String serviceId, ServiceBroker serviceBroker)
      Records an association between a Catalog.Service (represented here by the serviceId parameter) and the ServiceBroker responsible for it, and returns any ServiceBroker previously responsible for the association.

      Calls the CompositeServiceBroker.handleRemoveServiceBroker(ServiceBroker) method supplying it the supplied serviceBroker and returns the result.
      protected void CompositeServiceBroker.removeServices(ServiceBroker serviceBroker)
      Effectively emoves all Catalog.Services associated with the supplied ServiceBroker from being visible or known about in any way by this CompositeServiceBroker during an invocation of the CompositeServiceBroker.removeServiceBroker(ServiceBroker) method immediately before the supplied ServiceBroker is removed from this CompositeServiceBroker by the CompositeServiceBroker.handleRemoveServiceBroker(ServiceBroker) method.
